    "#! /usr/bin/env python3\n",
    "#encoding: utf-8\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import numpy.linalg as lin\n",
    "import cv2 \n",
    "import sys\n",
    "from rigidBody import *\n",
    "from areEqual import *"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "db2fcfe5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Definición de funciones auxiliares\n",
    "\n",
    "* ##### isInteger (s)\n",
    "\n",
    "Determina si el parámetro `s` es un entero\n",
    "\n",
    "Devuelve verdadero o falso acorde al resultado"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "62a7c03c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def isInteger (s):\n",
    "   try:\n",
    "      int(s)\n",
    "      return True\n",
    "   except ValueError:\n",
    "      return False"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7ac27d9b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* ##### areEqual (a, b, ord)\n",
    "\n",
    "Compara las cantidades reales `a` y `b`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Retorna `True` si ambas cantidades son iguales hasta el decimal `ord`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Retorna `False` en caso contrario. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "f323526b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def areEqual(a, b, ord):\n",
    "   if a == b:\n",
    "      return True\n",
    "   if a != 0. and b != 0.:\n",
    "      val = np.abs((a-b)/max(np.abs([a,b])))\n",
    "   else:\n",
    "      val = max(np.abs([a,b]));\n",
    "   if -np.log10(val) > ord:\n",
    "      return True;\n",
    "   return False"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d20c9f32",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* ##### normPH (P)\n",
    "\n",
    "Normaliza una matriz `P` que contiene coordenadas homogéneas"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "5811ff96",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def normPH(P):\n",
    "   r, c = P.shape\n",
    "   if r > 2:\n",
    "      lr = r - 1\n",
    "      for i in range(c):\n",
    "         P[:,i] /= P[lr, i]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "11d4c519",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* ##### skew (v)\n",
    "\n",
    "Calcula la matriz antisimétrica del vector `v`\n",
    "\n",
    "Transforma el vector `v` a la matriz `skv` y retorna la diferencia con su transpuesta.\n",
    "\n",
    "(Exactamente como lo transforma y qué es la matriz `skv`??)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "45346a58",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def skew(v):\n",
    "    skv = np.roll(np.roll(np.diag(v.flatten()),1,1),-1,0)\n",
    "    return skv - skv.T"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ebe39a86",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* ##### rodriguesRot (v)\n",
    "\n",
    "Usa la formula Rodrigues para calcular la matriz de rotación que corresponde a una rotación de ||`v`|| radianes alrededor de la rotación definida por el vector normal `v` / ||`v`||"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "b11b2e89",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def rodriguesRot(v):\n",
    "    theta = np.linalg.norm(v)\n",
    "    v = v / theta\n",
    "    omega = skew(v)\n",
    "    return np.eye(3) + np.sin(theta) * omega + (1.-np.cos(theta)) * np.dot(omega,omega)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "548c5e48",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* ##### logSO3 (R)\n",
    "\n",
    "Calcula el eje de rotacion `w` y el ángulo de rotación `theta` de la matriz de rotación `R`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Primero confirma que `R` es una matriz de rotación validando las propiedades conocidas (R @ R.R == eye(3) and |R| = +1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "b6155b99",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def logSO3(R):\n",
    "    if not areEqual(np.linalg.det(R), 1, 6) or not areEqual(np.linalg.norm(R@R.T-np.eye(3)),0, 6):\n",
    "        print('Error en logSO3: R no es una matriz de Rotación')\n",
    "        return None, None\n",
    "\n",
    "    theta = np.arccos((np.trace(R)-1)/2)\n",
    "    if theta != 0:\n",
    "        w = (1/(2*np.sin(theta)))*np.array([[R[2,1]-R[1,2]],[R[0,2]-R[2,0]],[R[1,0]-R[0,1]]])\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        w = np.array([1,0,0]).reshape(3,1) #Un vector arbitrario pues theta = 0\n",
    "    return w.reshape(3,), float(theta),"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "83fadbc5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* ##### ortGramSchmidt (v1, v2)\n",
    "\n",
    "Usa el algoritmo Gram-Schmidt para hacer `v1` y `v2` ortogonales."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "27834c96",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def ortGramSchmidt(v1, v2):\n",
    "    v2 = v2 - (v2 @ v1) * v1\n",
    "    n = v2 @ v2\n",
    "    if n == 0:\n",
    "        print(\"ERROR in ortGramSchmidt\")\n",
    "    v2 = v2 / np.sqrt(n)\n",
    "    return v1, v2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d6ce5559",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
